Package: rebirth
Title: Local Large Language Models as Base-R Objects
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Alessandro", "Vadala", , "vadale93@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Load and run local large language models (through a vendored,
    patched 'llama.cpp') from R and expose generation, embeddings, and
    mechanistic interpretability tools -- activation tracing, steering,
    and ablation -- as plain data frames and matrices in base-R idiom. The
    package is in early development (repository scaffold): no modelling
    functionality is available yet.
License: MIT + file LICENSE | Apache License (== 2.0)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.5.0)
Imports:
    nanoarrow
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 8.0.0
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/rextendr/version: 0.5.0
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc >= 1.71.0, cmake (>= 3.28), xz
